<%= Msh::Documentation.prelude %>

== name

msh - <%= Msh.gemspec.summary %>

== synopsis

*msh* [_options_]... [_file_]...

== description

Msh is a simple shell running inside a ruby interpreter. It supports a small subset of `sh`.

  - `[x]` pipelines
  - `[ ]` command grouping
  - `[ ]` subshells
  - `[ ]` conditionals
  - `[ ]` multiple commands
  - `[x]` simple commands
  - `[ ]` redirection

Additionally, it preprocesses your input as ERB, evaluated in the context of the shell, so you always have access to Ruby

    #{a = Date.today}
    echo "#{a}"
    cowsay #{IRB.start}

See <%= Msh.help_topics.reject { |t| t == "msh" }.sort.map { |topic| "msh-#{topic}(1)" }.join ", " %>.

== options

*-h, --help*::
  Show usage information.

*-V, --version*::
  Show the version.

*--copyright, --license*::
  Show the copyright.

*-c <command>*::
  Run a command string as input.

